<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06029058 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06029058 </ACCESS><CAPTION>  Photo; PHOTO: Bob Hope...Coming to San Jose  </CAPTION><LEADPARA>  COMEDIAN BOB HOPE, who entertained U.S. troops in the Persian Gulf atChristmas, will perform at Santa Clara University's 25th anniversary GoldenCircle Theater Party on Saturday at the San Jose Center for the PerformingArts.;    Also on the card for the black-tie gala is singer Pia Zadora.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Local  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  BOB HOPE TO HEADLINE CELEBRATION  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  The Valley Log  </MEMO><TEXT>     The show starts at 5:30 p.m. and will be followed by a dinner and dance atthe Fairmont Hotel in San Jose.;    Tickets are available from theuniversity's development office, (408) 554-4400. They are $250 each, or $325for seats in rows 3 through 11. Tickets are $125 for Santa Clara Universitygraduates of 1986 or later.;    Proceeds will benefit a variety of facilitiesand programs at the 140-year-old Jesuit university.; COMING; TRANSIT PLAN TOBE DISCUSSED;    A public information and discussion session on a railtransportation master plan for Santa Clara County is scheduled for 5:30 p.m.Wednesday in the lower-level cafeteria of the county administration building,770 W. Hedding St., San Jose.;    The meeting will focus on a 50-year visionfor rail transit in and around Santa Clara County. Source books withbackground information will be provided to all participants. To reserve aspace at the session, call the transportation agency's planning office at(408) 299-3141 by today.; (hbox);    An awards banquet sponsored by severalorganizations to honor people and groups who have instituted effectivealcohol-control measures is scheduled for noon Thursday at Le Baron Hotel,1350 N. First St., San Jose.;    The program will include a keynote speech byDr. Alan Blum of Baylor University's medical school. Admission costs $20.;(hbox);    The Visiting Nurse Association Hospice is offering a support groupfor those who have suffered loss of a loved one. The group meets Tuesdays at5:30 p.m. at the association office, 2025 Gateway Place, Suite 270, San Jose.;   For more information, call Miriam Vinton, (408) 452-1224.  </TEXT><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  SAN JOSE MERCURY NEWS  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910129  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Tuesday  </DAY><MONTH>  January  </MONTH><PG.COL>  2B  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><FEATURE>  PHOTO  </FEATURE><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  327  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Tuesday January 29, 199100029058,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>